## §4 Dissection Gate

The four conformance criteria, restated:

- **(a)** Every constant has a substrate-measured equivalent with declared provenance.
- **(b)** Every named theorem invoked is expressible as a composition of registered transitions from substrate primitives.
- **(c)** The substrate-native implementation either bit-matches the original implementation, or documented divergences exist with the substrate-native version treated as authoritative.
- **(d)** The modelling commitments the original locks in — choices alternative articulations would have made differently — are declared in the layer manifest.

A module is **dissected** iff all four hold. Anything less is **not yet dissected** (binary verdict per §4).

