## Recommended ordering: first three transplantation tasks

The transplantation queue is ordered by **capability spread × architectural prerequisite chain**, not by dissection cost. Three candidates dominate, in this order:

### Transplant 1 — Conditioning / ULP primitive (GAP-003)

**Rationale.** `SUBSTRATE_CONSTRUCTION.md §9 step 1` explicitly names this as the prerequisite for V3 transplants: *"The conditioning primitive (instrument geometry on the IEEE 754 float lattice) is implemented and stabilised. This is prerequisite to most subsequent transplants because many V3 methods compose against conditioning structures."* This is direct guidance from the methodology.

Capability spread: VERY HIGH. Closes DRY-003 (8+ duplicated ULP helpers); unlocks GAP-004 (BACL grain), GAP-005 (K_G), and the entire BACL/c2/Conjecture-C dependency chain.

Dissection-gate distance: medium. Eight scratch ULP implementations exist; differences are subnormal handling. A canonical typed primitive will resolve drift.

**Why first:** the methodology document explicitly names it. Its absence makes every downstream substrate transplant depend on ad-hoc ULP helpers.

### Transplant 2 — Hardened dual-arm probe lift (GAP-011)

**Rationale.** This is a *lifecycle* transplant (not a substrate-construction transplant in the §3 sense), but it has three properties that make it the natural second:

1. **Independent of GAP-001/002/003 chains.** It is not blocked by any of the Axiom 11′ work.
2. **Production-active.** Per `LIVE_CAMPAIGNS_LEDGER` `hardened-dual-arm-probe`, V1 is operative; the architectural debt is the only reason it sits in scratch/.
3. **Self-contained.** No substrate primitives need to be invented; the probe composes only against existing L1 primitives + L2 metrology.

Capability spread: HIGH-LOCALISED. Closes one specific architectural debt with no chain-of-dependencies.

Dissection-gate distance: nearest of all candidates (passes b/c operationally; needs (a) typing tightness + (d) LAYER_MANIFEST entry).

**Why second:** can be done in parallel with Transplant 1; provides a fast architectural win and a worked example of the §3 transplantation methodology at the L3 instrument level. Operationally, the substrate gains nothing new — but the *layering* becomes honest.

### Transplant 3 — Typed sqrt + typed log primitive bundle (GAP-001 + GAP-002)

**Rationale.** These two are tightly coupled (both required for `typed_log_log_slope` and `directional_alpha_probe` to be Axiom-11′-compliant) and naturally land together. The pair closes the Axiom 11 → Axiom 11′ refinement criterion 1 for the most-used named-math substrate calls (`math.sqrt`, `math.log`).

Capability spread: VERY HIGH. Together they touch every substrate primitive currently violating Axiom 11 strict form (4 primitives + 1 L2 module). Sets up Axiom 11′ activation per `SUBSTRATE_CONSTRUCTION.md §7.1`.

Dissection-gate distance: medium. The substrate-native implementation can call `math.sqrt` / `math.log` internally during construction (the IEEE-754-correct rounding behaviour is itself substrate-traceable through BACL + Conjecture C); the gating work is wrapping these in typed envelopes with declared status families and provenance.

**Why third:** done after Transplant 1 because the typed_sqrt / typed_log primitives may want to compose against the new conditioning primitive (the precision_floor concept and the unit-roundoff lookup are conditioning information).

